President Obama has proclaimed October 2013 as National Energy Action Month in order to address the challenges of the 21st century and ensure a clean, safe, and sustainable energy future. The proclamation emphasizes the progress made in increasing energy security, reducing oil imports, and promoting renewable energy sources. However, it also acknowledges the need for further action to minimize waste, increase clean energy production, reduce carbon pollution, and develop new advanced technologies. The President calls for international cooperation and engagement to tackle global energy challenges and emphasizes the potential of a clean energy economy to fuel long-term economic growth. The proclamation concludes by urging citizens to work together to achieve greater energy security, a robust economy, and a healthier environment for future generations.